description:
## Severity
Minor

## Dimension
Perimeter Defense / Error Orchestration

## Location
src/tools/file/list.rs:17-24 (execute_list_files iteration)

## Violation
```rust
for entry in entries.flatten() {
    ...
}
```

`flatten()` on a `Result` iterator silently drops every error, returning only successful items. A directory containing a symlink the process cannot stat returns a partial listing with no indication that an entry was skipped. The model believes it has the complete directory contents and may decide a file does not exist when in fact stat failed for that file.

Same pattern is used in file_index.rs:55 with the same defect — but that one is for a recursive index where the cost is even higher (entire subtrees silently dropped).

## Mandated refactor
Replace with explicit loop and tracing::warn! on errors:
```rust
for entry in entries {
    match entry {
        Ok(e) => { ... items.push ... },
        Err(e) => { tracing::warn!(path=%path.display(), error=%e, "list_files: failed to read entry"); skipped += 1; }
    }
}
if skipped > 0 { items.push(format!("[{} entries skipped due to errors — see logs]", skipped)); }
```

